      • angleEncoder

        public Mk2SwerveModuleBuilder angleEncoder(AnalogInput encoder,
                                           double offset)
        Configures the swerve module to use an analog encoder through one of the RoboRIO's analog input ports.
        Parameters:
        encoder - The analog input handle to use for the encoder.
        offset - The offset of the encoder in radians. This value is added to the analog encoder reading to obtain the true module angle.
        Returns:
        The builder.

      • angleMotor

        public Mk2SwerveModuleBuilder angleMotor(CANSparkMax motor)
        Configures the swerve module to use a CAN Spark MAX driving a NEO as it's angle motor.

        The default PID constants and angle reduction are used. These values have been determined to work with all Mk2 modules controlled by this motor.

        To override this values see angleMotor(CANSparkMax, PidConstants, double)

        Parameters:
        motor - The CAN Spark MAX to use as the angle motor. The NEO's encoder is set to output the module's angle in radians.
        Returns:
        The builder.

      • angleMotor

      • angleMotor

        public Mk2SwerveModuleBuilder angleMotor(CANSparkMax motor,
                                         PidConstants constants,
                                         double reduction)
        Configures the swerve module to use a CAN Spark MAX driving a NEO as it's angle motor.

        This method is usually used when custom PID tuning is required. If using the standard angle reduction and a NEO, angleMotor(CANSparkMax) uses already tuned constants so no tuning is required.

        Parameters:
        motor - The CAN Spark MAX to use as the angle motor. The NEO's encoder is set to output the module's angle in radians.
        constants - The PID constants to use to control the module's angle (units are in radians).
        reduction - The reduction of the angle motor. It should be specified so the number is greater than 1. For example, an 18:1 ratio should be specified by 18.0 / 1.0.
        Returns:
        The builder.

        Configures the swerve module to use a PWM Spark MAX driving a NEO as it's angle motor.

        The default PID constants are used. These values have been determined to work with all Mk2 modules controlled by a NEO using the standard angle reduction.

        Parameters:

        public Mk2SwerveModuleBuilder angleMotor(SpeedController motor,
                                         PidConstants constants)
        Configures the swerve module to use a generic speed controller as it's angle motor.

        This method is usually used when custom PID tuning is required or a NEO is not used.

        Parameters:

        constants - The PID constants to use to control the module's angle (units are in radians).
        Returns:
        The builder.

      • driveMotor

        public Mk2SwerveModuleBuilder driveMotor(CANSparkMax motor)
        Configures the swerve module to use a CAN Spark MAX driving a NEO as it's drive motor.

        The default reduction and wheel diameter are used. These will work with the recommended wheel and stock drive reduction. By default distance and velocity will be reported in inches and inches per second.

        Parameters:
        motor - The CAN Spark MAX to use as the drive motor. The NEO's encoder is set to output the module's driven distance and current velocity in inches and inches per second.
        Returns:
        The builder.

      • driveMotor

        public Mk2SwerveModuleBuilder driveMotor(CANSparkMax motor,
                                         Mk2SwerveModuleBuilder.MotorType motorType)

      • driveMotor

        public Mk2SwerveModuleBuilder driveMotor(CANSparkMax motor,
                                         double reduction,
                                         double wheelDiameter)
        Configures the swerve module to use a CAN Spark MAX driving a NEO as it's drive motor.
        Parameters:
        motor - The CAN Spark MAX to use as the drive motor. The NEO's encoder is set to output the module's driven distance and current velocity. Units are the same as the units used for the wheel diameter.
        reduction - The drive reduction of the module. It should be specified so the number is greater than 1. For example, an 18:1 ratio should be specified by 18.0 / 1.0.
        wheelDiameter - The diameter of the module's wheel. By default this is inches.
        Returns:
        The builder.
